Options.OPTION[StarQWorkflowKit.StarQWor:
DISCLAIMER: This mod modifies prefabs in an irreversible way. Please ensure you have a backup of your processing folder before using it, as changes cannot be undone. The mod author is not responsible for any loss of content resulting from its use.
A game restart is absolutely necessary most of the time for the modified assets to be shown up in game.
If any prefabs from mods_subscribed is modified using any of the methods below, it will change the file integrity of the Prefab thus will show up as 'dirty/modified' is Simple Mod Checker's mod verification. To restore, simply delete the folder and let the game (or Skyve) redownload it for you.
WARNING: Do not process files if you've received any errors for that asset on game startup.
Folder path to create packages from
Options.OPTION_DESCRIPTION[StarQWorkflow:
Create <cok> package to **StreamingData~\\~CreatedPackages**
This will create one package for the whole selected path. No prefab processing will be done, but supports subfolders.
The packages won't be available in-game by default, since that will conflict with the original prefab files.
Remove/disable the original prefab folder and move the <.cok> files out of the **~CreatedPackages** folder (or remove the ~ in front of **~CreatedPackages**) to test the package in-game.

StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.PrefabMustBeActive:
Move all files you want to add to a separate folders in **StreamingData~** and input that folder; which you can then take it to it's original folder.
** * **s are supported for paths like **\\A*\\B** or **\\A\\\\*\\B**.
Prefabs in this folder must be existing in the folder before the game is loaded. Will not work for disabled folders (with . or ~ in front). Will not work for folders outside the game's scope.
StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.ResaveReason: can be used in the event of changed prefab structure, resetting id/type after manually editing prefab, or to recreate CID if not found
StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.PrefabID: The PrefabID is the name of the prefab that is shown in the Editor's Edit Prefab list, not the localized name.
StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.EditorCatsWarning: IMPORTANT: Saving prefabs with this enable will have the category saved on the prefab file itself. Make sure to remove it manually before saving if you don't want it to be saved, or resave using the <Prefab Resave> buttons above.
